It's not amazing.

00:54:15.000 --> 00:54:19.000
Like, you know, the context in this particular case is pretty small.

00:54:20.000 --> 00:54:28.000
And in particular, if you think about how that embedding thing worked, you can't really use, like, the normal kind of follow-up.

00:54:28.000 --> 00:54:34.000
So, for example, now the problem is that there's no context here being sent to the embedding model.

00:54:34.000 --> 00:54:37.000
So it's actually going to have no idea I'm talking about ULMFIT.

00:54:37.000 --> 00:54:41.000
So generally speaking, it's going to do a terrible job.

